During the Vietnam War the great pacifist A.J.Muste stood in front of the White House night after night with a candle.
Asked &ldquo;Do you really think you'll change the country this way?&rdquo;
Muste answered &ldquo;I don't do this to change the country. I do this so the country won't change me.&rdquo;
This is my purpose in creating this web site.
I remain committed to the UK being part of the EU.

Lots of rubbish in the campaign about the EU imposing rules on us and not a lot about the fact that we agreed with nearly all of them and for those few we opposed we were always on the wrong side of the argument.
Fortunately, someone has done the hard work and anaylsed all of the individual laws and provided a neat summary on Twitter.
